    <!-- Chosen Palette: "Calm Harmony" - A palette grounded in warm neutrals (bg-stone-50, text-slate-800) with complementary colors for components (stone-200, stone-800) and subtle accents (blue-600, amber-500, green-600) to represent the three companies. -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA uses a "Relationship-Centric Dashboard" design. Instead of following the report's linear structure, it starts with a visual, interactive diagram of the three companies' relationships. Clicking a relationship (e.g., Apple-Samsung) dynamically updates a content pane, providing a high-level summary. This encourages non-linear exploration. Users can then scroll or use the sticky navigation to dive deeper into thematic sections: 'The Financials' (with interactive charts), 'The Battlegrounds' (with a timeline and comparative analysis), and 'The Future' (with summary cards). This structure was chosen to make the complex web of dependencies immediately understandable and to allow users to explore based on their interest (e.g., finance, history, strategy) rather than forcing them through a long text. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: The core co-opetitive relationships. -> Goal: Organize/Relate. -> Viz: HTML/CSS interactive diagram. -> Interaction: Click on a relationship line to update a dynamic text pane with a summary. -> Justification: Visually represents the central "entangled" theme and is more engaging than static text. -> Method: Vanilla JS with Tailwind-styled divs.
        - Report Info: Financial data (Google-Apple deal, company revenues). -> Goal: Compare/Inform. -> Viz: Bar and Donut charts. -> Interaction: Hover tooltips for precise data. -> Justification: Best method for visualizing trends and proportions clearly. -> Library: Chart.js.
        - Report Info: Apple vs. Samsung patent litigation history. -> Goal: Show Change. -> Viz: Vertical timeline. -> Interaction: None needed; focus is on clear chronological presentation. -> Justification: Standard, effective format for historical events. -> Method: HTML/CSS with Tailwind.
        - Report Info: Future disruptors. -> Goal: Inform/Summarize. -> Viz: Card-based layout. -> Interaction: Minimal hover effects. -> Justification: Easily digestible, scannable format for key takeaways. -> Method: HTML/CSS with Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
