                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">The Decade-Long Patent War: Apple vs. Samsung</h3>
                        <div class="relative pl-8">
                            <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 h-full w-0.5 bg-slate-300"></div>
                            <div class="relative mb-8">
                                <div class="absolute -left-[38px] top-1 w-4 h-4 bg-blue-600 rounded-full border-4 border-slate-100"></div>
                                <p class="font-semibold text-blue-700">2011: The First Shot</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">Apple sues Samsung, alleging it "slavishly copied" the iPhone's design patents, including its rounded corners and icon grid.</p>
                            </div>
                             <div class="relative mb-8">
                                <div class="absolute -left-[38px] top-1 w-4 h-4 bg-blue-600 rounded-full border-4 border-slate-100"></div>
                                <p class="font-semibold text-blue-700">2012: The Billion-Dollar Verdict</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">A U.S. jury awards Apple over $1 billion in damages, a stunning victory that ignites years of appeals.</p>
                            </div>
                             <div class="relative mb-8">
                                <div class="absolute -left-[38px] top-1 w-4 h-4 bg-blue-600 rounded-full border-4 border-slate-100"></div>
                                <p class="font-semibold text-blue-700">2016: The Supreme Court Weighs In</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">The Supreme Court rules on how design patent damages are calculated, a partial victory for Samsung that remands the case.</p>
                            </div>
                             <div class="relative">
                                <div class="absolute -left-[38px] top-1 w-4 h-4 bg-blue-600 rounded-full border-4 border-slate-100"></div>
                                <p class="font-semibold text-blue-700">2018: The Truce</p>
                                <p class="text-slate-600">After a final retrial awards Apple $539 million, the two giants finally reach a confidential settlement, ending the war.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">The Ad Wars: Marketing as a Weapon</h3>
                        <div class="space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-blue-700">Samsung: The Aggressive Challenger</h4>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 mt-2">Relentlessly mocks Apple in ads, highlighting features the iPhone lacks (zoom, foldables) and poking fun at Apple fans waiting in line. Strategy: Position Galaxy as the innovative alternative.</p>
                            </div>
                             <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-green-700">Google: The Snarky Alternative</h4>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 mt-2">Uses clever, pointed ads to position Pixel as the "smarter" phone, highlighting its AI features and criticizing Apple's slow adoption of standards like RCS messaging.</p>
                            </div>
                             <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow">
                                <h4 class="font-bold text-lg text-gray-700">Apple: The Aloof Leader</h4>
                                <p class="text-slate-600 mt-2">Stays above the fray, never mentioning competitors. Focuses on premium quality, user experience, and emotional connection ("Shot on iPhone"). Strategy: Reinforce its status as the industry benchmark that all others compare themselves to.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
